column30: Koha is an open source web based library management system in use in thousands of libraries worldwide.  With Koha\, as well as public access\, library staff access to the system is completely web-based; acquisitions\, circulation\, cataloguing\, serials and reports are all done through a web browser.  As well as an excellent search engine the public catalogue offers a range of Web 2.0 and Library 2.0 facilities such as tagging\, commenting and public and private lists.   Key to the success of any library automation project are the full range of implementation services provided by PTFS Europe\, these include; training\, data conversion\, project management\, server hosting and high quality on-going annual support.  Customers in the UK using Koha include the National Archives\, the Defence Academy of the UK (Barrington Library)\, Kettering NHS Foundation Trust\, Tavistock and Portman NHS Foundation Trust\, Herefordshire NHS Libraries\, Worcestershire NHS Libraries and Staffordshire University.

Cloud Readiness Assessment ? a review of an organisation?s current technology estate to determine the potential opportunities\, costs and risks associated with introduction of PaaS\, IaaS or SaaS technology.  ? Cloud Strategy and Architecture ? advice regarding the optimum strategic approach for cloud services\, with particular emphasis on the design of an appropriate architectural framework in which to deploy cloud computing services.  It also covers advice for selection and procurement of cloud computing components.? Cloud Planning ? advice on the optimum approach for implementation of cloud components\, including work planning\, resource estimation\, risk assessment\, and costing of cloud programmes. This service is a natural extension of our systems integration services and includes the design\, implementation and testing of interfaces between cloud computing components (SaaS\, PaaS and IaaS) and on-premise technology.  It includes: ? Design of custom interfaces between cloud and on-premise technology; ? Development of custom integration between published cloud APIs and existing technology components\, or between multiple divers cloud deployments; ? Development of extensions to SaaS products and services to provide additional functionality or capability; ? Development of customised solutions to provide extended functionality to complement deployed cloud services.

RepKnight is a listening and analysis platform
The application monitors the networks 24x7x365 for keywords (areas of interest) identifying results\, 24/7\, in real time.
It collates these results and analyses the sentiment within the collection of messages\, underlying and emerging topics\, and the key influencers and menbers of the networks of users within the results.
We monitor the Twitter firehose\, Facebook\, Google+\, YouTube\, Flickr\, blogs\, news sites collating a holistic view from the 100?s of million of users talking on the networks\, enabling engagement on the networks in a fully audited fashion.
All captured information is stored in the databases and available for access 24/7/365. Example uses include identifying emerging incidents such as riots\, strikes and the Occupy movement in real time.

column25: IBM Network Infrastructure Optimisation for Cloud
column30:
This service has been developed to help organisations better understand their network\, and the implications on the network of migrating workload or provisioning services via a Cloud.

The LAN/WAN optimization assessment will address the following areas:
- Performance to meet end-user and application response times required for high productivity
- Scalability that may allow you to expand or contract the network\, with limited disruption and expense\, in 
  response to significant shifts in your business environment
- Security features that may protect the integrity of your information as it traverses your network\, against a variety of perils and threats\, while maintaining privacy
- Modularity for using open architecture standards to allow for selection and use of the best products on the market
- Adherence to industry standards that can help enable easier integration of diverse components and systems into a high-performance network

For more information\, please visit: ibm.com/services/integratedcommunications

column25: IBM Migration to Cloud - Workload Analysis
column30:
After you have defined your cloud strategy\, you may want to further analyse the fit of your proposed targeted clouds with actual workloads before embarking on the detailed planning and design for a migration project.  An  analysis of your application workloads can help identify candidate applications for the target cloud environment(s) and can help you gain an understanding of the viability\, operational cost changes and migration impact. This service helps you to answer the following questions:
- Can the workload run in the target cloud environment? Is it compatible with my infrastructure\, middleware and operating system image?
- Can the target cloud environment satisfy my performance\, availability and other nonfunctional requirements?
- Can the target cloud environment comply with applicable security\, privacy and regulatory requirements?
- What benefits can we realize from migration? (For example\, can we lower overall operating costs? Improve service levels?)
- How challenging might it be to get to cloud given my current workloads?

To learn more about the IBM Workload Transformation Analysis for Cloud\, please visit the following website: ibm.com/services/itsaconsulting

Fujitsu?s Business Case Service is a professional consultancy exercise that will produce an outline business case (OBC)\, for a Programme to implement an identified Cloud service.  This will formalise the objectives of and the reasons for\, the Cloud Programme.  It will indicate alignment with organisation strategy\, the level of investment needed and the potential return.
The output from the Cloud Business Case service will allow the Customer to make an informed decision as to whether to proceed further with the Programme of work and if so\, what level of investment is required.
A pre-requisite for the delivery of this Service is that the Customer has used the associated Fujitsu Cloud Executive Workshop and Cloud Roadmapping Services\, as these provide input to the production of the Outline Business Case (OBC).

The Fujitsu Cloud Executive Workshop provides senior business executives with greater insight into cloud computing and generates an increased understanding of how they can take advantage of these technologies.  
The Cloud Executive Workshop has been designed as a highly interactive ?executive discussion? session which will cover business and market trends\, benefits of Cloud adoption and the issues and challenges surrounding Cloud computing. The session will be facilitated by Fujitsu cloud experts representing consulting\, business and technology centres of excellence.  
This workshop will enable the Customer to understand what types of Cloud services would be most appropriate and how these will support their organisation and IT objectives.  It will also help build commitment to emerging Cloud programmes.

column30:
The Fujitsu Cloud Roadmapping Service is a workshop that involves both Business and IT teams in building a roadmap/project plan related to the introduction of specific Cloud services.  It will act as a change management tool to drive plans and accelerate the transformation to the cloud in identified and prioritised areas.  This will build consensus among staff involved in the process.
The Fujitsu Cloud Roadmapping Service will enable the Customer to achieve faster deployment of\, and reduced risk in\, implementing Cloud services. 
This can be run as a half or full-day session\, depending on the scope of the workshop.
The success of this session is dependent on availability and active engagement of Customer decision-makers.
A pre-requisite to the delivery of this service is that the client undertakes the Fujitsu Cloud Executive Workshop.

The Unifier platform utilises many existing and experienced applications to accomplish an immersion of the user\, such as SmartFox and Flash Voice. It has been tested on Internet Explorer\, Firefox\, Opera and Safari as well as Apple OS and Microsoft operating systems. column30: Emergn's Expert Advice service offering is designed to help our customers with ongoing access to practical thought-leadership and our team of agile experts and research. Expert Advice provides customers with the opportunity to tailor service to their specific requirements. This can range from advice onhow to approach an Agile Change Program through to a view on how an existing agile approach is working. This service will also provide access to the latest thinking around agile and solving complex problems. The Mentoring service offering in Emergn?s Advisory area is focused on the individual in the organisation that is interested in leveraging the benefits of executive coaching but with the added need for domain experience and learning especially as it relates to applying agile practices and principles in their respective role. This can be applied effectively in their current role either for on-going requirements or to solve immediate challenges.

Emergn understand that working in an agile way includes the full end-to-end cycle\, from concept to delivery. As well as building the solutions right\, we must also esnure the right solutions are being built. Our consulting covers how to apply agile thinking to portfolio management\, financial management\, sourcing\, vendor management\, contracting as well as the process and engineering principles required to deliver solutions.

Emergn understand the difficulty identifying and recruiting the people with the appropriate skills and experience in running and delivering agile programmes & projects. This service allows of customer to confidently source people and teams with a proved track record. Emergn are happy to supply the breath of needs from individual key roles to full teams.

Our unique method of practical action learning brings Agile and Lean to life in your organization. What you learn today\, you apply tomorrow at your workplace to give you immediate results.Our education programmes explore first principles ? the why behind problems and solutions. This allows you to examine your organization?s unique challenges and feel confident in creating a working\, practical approach suitable for your organization.

column25: DDS Secure SharePoint 2010 Service for Team Collaboration
column30: The DDS Team Collaboration Service is a multi-tenancy implementation of Microsoft SharePoint 2010\,operated from the GSi-connected\, IL3-accredited GWS environment. The service is aimed at government projects that require fast access to a secure SharePoint facility for multi-agency usage. The service is supported by a full service wrap and has some high performance capabilities such as support for multi-media handling\, optional single-sign-on (via the DDS SaaS Identity Federation Service)\,  and self-service user management (via the DDS Cloud User Portal). Instances of the service can be procured on a per month basis with no more thana  monthly commitment; termination being at no charge

column25: DDS Secure SharePoint 2010 Service for Departmental EDRM
column30: The DDS Departmental EDRM Collaboration Service is a multi-tenancy implementation of Microsoft SharePoint 2010\, operated from the GSi-connected\, IL3-accredited GWS environment. The service provides a SharePoint Records Management capability aimed at government departments intending  to use SharePoint to manage their documents and records. The service has a full service wrap and offers some high performance technical capabilities such as support for multi-media handling\, optional single-sign-on (via the DDS SaaS Identity Federation Service)\,  and self-service user management (via the DDS Cloud User Portal). The service is competitively priced against a commitment for a minimum one year  period.

The DDS Safe Box provides a secure file sharing capability for users in different government agencies to securely exhange data. The solution re-uses two DDS G-Cloud servcie - the DDS SharePoint 2010 service (for storage and workflow) and the DDS Cloud User Portal (fro fast provisioning). The file exchange process is an ayschronous control system that alters users to transfers awaiting them\, and the option of applying extra security to file exchanges\, such as  limiting the time  the data is available\, automatically deleting daat after collection\, etc.. The current service is accredited to IL3 and there are plans in the Roadmap for an IL2-IL3 version. Users use a GSi (or equivalent) secure connection to use the current release of this service; accessing the portal through standard HTTPS. The service supports for digital media file transfers  making it a suitable exchange mechanism for agencies needing to carry out high  volume exchanges. A full service wrap is included with the service and the service can be procured on a per user per month basis with no more than a  monthly commitment; termination being at no charge

column25: DDS Secure SharePoint 2010 Service for Criminal Justice
column30: The DDS Criminal Justice Collaboration Service is a multi-tenancy implementation of Microsoft SharePoint 2010\, operated from the IL3-accredited GWS environment. With connectivity from both the GSi and CJX communities\, this multi-agency service will help agencies in the criminal justice domain share their information securely across agency boundaries. The service has a full service wrap and includes a number of CJS focused SharePoint capabilities such as support for digital media handling\, (e.g.: for digital evidence)\, and digital forms processing\, making them very appropriate for Police and CPS case management work. Instances of the service can be procured on a per month basis with no more than a  monthly commitment; termination being at no charge

DDS Organisational Directory system provides searchable 'White' & 'Yellow Pages' database of the organisation's staff\, functions\, teams\, projects\, office locations\,  with auto-sycnhronised and self-service portal. The Directory supports open standards such as LDAP and synchronisation features that allow it to provide a searchable front-end integrating an organisation's staff and team information held in sources such as Active Directory and the HR system.

The DDS Skills Directory offers a powerful directory of Staff Skills and Knowledge that's seachable over the organisation's staff\, functions\, teams\, projects\, and office locations. This gives staff a full "white and yellow pages" view of an organisation and its partners.  The system has a rich set of synchronisation options that enable it to link easily with Active Directory and other HR databases. The Skills Directory maps onto the government's 'Competency Framework'\, is fully searchable and  has features like 'mentoring' that enable it to be used for activelly managing staff resourcing\, development and training

The DDS Identity Federation Service is an identity broker solution that gives government users seamless single-sign-on to secure G-Cloud services.  The system includes a local directory and use rprofile system that gives organisations the option for holding local users accounts for groups users that operate from un-federated networks\, thus extending the scope of the system. For service suppliers\, this is a low cost way of giving their services a single-sign-on capability\, and for local user\, removing the burden of managing secondary user accounts and password resets.

The DDS Secure CRM Service is based on Microsoft Dynamics CRM platform to provide government agencies\, departments and projects with the ability to utilise quickly deploy CRM busienss solutions for reducing costs and improving current working practices. The DDS CRM service is security accredited to IL3 and optimised for government. DDS incldues a servcie wrap that is designed to amplify user adoption\, help organisations discover new business insights\, and fuel business productivity across the entire business network.  The service is delivred through the Savvis GWS serbice and is accessible to users via the government GSi network. Instances of the service can be procured on a per month basis with no more than a  monthly commitment; termination being at no charge

column25: DDS Secure Cloud User Portal Service
column30: The DDS Cloud User Portal provides a mechanism for managing the deployment and usage of secure SaaS services. Government customers can use the Portal to lookup\, procure and provision SaaS services\, and subsequently to manage their ongoing usage and billing. Service suppliers can use the portal as a SaaS product marketplace\, where the automated procurement\, usage and charging capabilities provide a usage-based billing interface into eProcurement systems such as GeM.

BiP?s Delta eSourcing is a cutting-edge eSourcing service allowing public sector organisations to achieve efficiency savings and tackle escalating costs.
Delta modules provide:
? e-Notice - publish your opportunities and automatically transmit OJEU-level contracts.
? Buyer portal - A Buyer Portal is a dedicated online area containing your organisation?s procurement related information and a wide range of contract announcements. The portal is fully compliant with UK Regulations and European Directives allowing you to inform your suppliers of your authority?s tender opportunities.
? Tender Manager - Delta eSourcing?s Tender Manager is an easy-to-use\, EU-compliant tender management service which provides a secure\, competitive tendering process from creation of notice to award of contract.
? Supplier Manager - Supplier Manager allows your organisation to quickly assess and qualify the best suppliers and negotiate the best value contracts.
? Contract Manager - Contract Manager is a centralised repository which facilitates the registration\, promotion and monitoring of all of your organisation?s contracts and agreements.
? eAuctions - eAuctions is a reverse auction tool compliant with EU Regulations which can be used as a stand-alone service or as an extension of your tender exercise.

Supply Chain Development is a service that allows purchasing authorities to support the
opening of their supply chains to local Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (SME?s). SCD
provides a portal through which a purchasing authority can make contract opportunities visible
to existing and potential suppliers. In addition\, the portal provides tools for the creation and
evaluation of pre-qualification questionnaires. Potential suppliers complete a business readiness
test during the registration process based on their formal policies and procedures. Where
necessary\, suppliers are directed to appropriate sources of assistance to make themselves
business ready.
 
Licensing of the portal and underlying tools not only allows the authority to make its
contract opportunities visible\, use is extended to the authority?s suppliers to enable them to
publicise their sub-contracting opportunities and use the selection tools.
The award winning CompeteFor.com portal is an example of the Supply Chain Development
toolkit and supporting service in operation. http://www.CompeteFor.com is fully hosted web
based electronic contract opportunity brokerage service that gives companies unique access to
business opportunities generated by the London 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Games and the
capability to bid for them. The CompeteFor.com portal is a free service for suppliers and the
chosen site for the publication of London 2012 Olympic Games-related contract opportunities.

With the new mandatory requirement for the UK public sector to publish spend transactions worth over 500 for local authorities and 25\,000 for central government\, public sector buyers and suppliers are now able to know more than ever before about their own organisation\, marketplace and position within it.

For public sector buyers\, Tracker Spend Analysis helps you:
? Manage risk
? Carry out market research for a Tender exercise
? Respond to Freedom of Information requests.
? Know how much/often other public bodies spend with your suppliers 
? Identify how much of your spend is with particular suppliers 
? Assess the level of risk and opportunity that your spend creates 
? Assess policy compliance and reduce maverick spending
? Create evidence-based\, realistic and achievable cost saving strategies
? Consider collaborative opportunities with similar buying organisations
? Identify potential for negotiation with existing suppliers
? Identify potential new suppliers
? Assess the economic impact of your spend on local businesses
? Help your supply base to develop their product offering
? Evaluate your spend's economic development/regeneration value
? Create accurate and meaningful responses to media and FOIA queries
? Compare your organisation's spend against similar public bodies
? Deliver realistic\, evidence-based strategies for increased efficiency
? Graph\, chart and analyse your spend and supply chain shape
? Track changing spend patterns and activity through stored searches.

VPN-Cubed VPN-Cubed provides an overlay network which is a computer network built on top of another network. Nodes in the overlay network can be thought of as being connected by virtual or logical links\, each of which corresponds to a path\, perhaps through many physical links\, in the underlying network.
Cloud-based overlay networks can be used to maintain control across multiple clouds (public\, private\, federated\, & hybrid)\, allowing the customer to control their own network topology\, the network addressing\, encrypted communication\, and desired network protocols\, all in a scalable\, highly redundant form.

HADRIAN is fully compliant with the CESG Supplier Information Assurance Assessment Framework and the Supplier Information Assurance Tool (SIAT) question sets and specification.  The solution is used by leading UK Government organisations\, including but not limited to Departments such as the Home Office\, the Ministry of Defence and Her Majesty's Revenue & Customs. column30:
Overview
Symantec Security Monitoring Services provide enterprise-wide log retention and real-time security monitoring of networks and security infrastructures\, enabling you to protect your information assets and demonstrate compliance with industry regulations. Symantec's streamlined collection architecture offloads log management burdens\, while sophisticated and comprehensive analysis alerts you to priority issues requiring attention. Comprehensive reporting informs you and your auditors. Your staff maintains full control of the network and security infrastructure at all times and can act proactively to prevent and mitigate problems.
Symantec Security Monitoring Services
By analyzing security incidents generated from alert and log data\, Symantec acquires a deep understanding of your network environment and threat activity\, and uses this information along with awareness of your vulnerabilities and the global threat environment to properly inform you on threats impacting your organization. The aggregation of log data is handled through encrypted connections to client security devices or aggregation points\, including select vendor management consoles or Symantec?s Log Collection Platform. At the Security Operations Centers (SOCs)\, aggregated data is mined and analyzed using a variety of advanced technologies and expert systems. Incidents are escalated according to a predefined process\, based on varying levels of criticality. Symantec analysts are always available to provide guidance that enables you to take defensive action against intrusions before an attack can spread and a loss of information can occur. Incident reports\, analysis\, and other key security data are available for review at all times on a secure Web portal.
Key benefits
? Real-time security monitoring to detect known and emerging threats enables timely response to incidents; mitigates risks to critical assets by prioritizing remediation.
? Highly available and secure storage of logs\, incidents\, and reports in industry certified facilities without the hassle of additional equipment\, management\, or expertise; complies with forensics best practices.
? Satisfies the compliance requirements of PCI DSS\, SOX\, and other industry regulations.
Symantec monitors the widest array of technology types of any Managed Security Service Provider including:
? Firewall
? Unified threat management
? Integrated security appliances
? Network intrusion detection
? Network intrusion prevention
? Network routers and switches
? Network behavioral analysis
? VPN concentrators
? Web gateway and proxy devices
? Web application firewalls
? Host intrusion detection

Socium?s cloud-based ?Online Validation Service? (OVS) enables public and private spatial data providers and users to quality assure / validate their data against a set of ?business rules?. These rules represent the user?s requirements as to their data?s content and structure\, how it is formatted and its adherence to any applicable standards. OVS users can either select appropriate rules to be applied from a standard OVS set or in conjunction with the team at Socium\, define them themselves using a powerful logic-based natural language syntax. Using OVS therefore allows spatial data providers and users to easily ensure that their data is fit for purpose and can be relied upon for sharing and making critical business decisions. column30: Addressing IT transformation and cloud services requires an information centric approach - one which considers the value of information to the user and to the enterprise. EMC combines a deep understanding of the IT business needs with knowledge of technical solutions to help companies deploy systems for managing information access and for meeting regulatory requirements.  EMC develops detailed functional cloud service specifications including system interfaces\, API specifications\, and data flows. Recommendations consider the criticality of the information and availability requirements.  By going onsite to review configurations and interview personnel\, EMC is able to assess technology\, operational practices\, and management policies. EMC provides a comprehensive approach to project specifications\, including reporting and retention requirements\, and defining requirements for analysis and correlation of events.
column38: SFIA Definitions Rate Card with rates FINAL 19Dec2011.doc
column270: Cloud Project Specification & Selection NEW V2-1.pdf

column30: EMC supports the deployment of a formal cloud services offering and associated multi-year cloud strategy to various Lines of Business (LOBs) to enable customers to optimize current technology investment\, gain greater operational efficiencies\, and simultaneously increase organizational agility to meet the increasing demands of the business to deliver critical services in a timely fashion at reduced price.  We help create service-based business models\, which include: Cloud Service Catalogue and the supporting costs\, tiers and levels of service; Cloud Service Level Agreements (SLAs); Cloud Service Consumption Reporting; Cloud Chargeback model with consumption based pricing
column38: SFIA Definitions Rate Card with rates FINAL 19Dec2011.doc

column30: The introduction of virtualization into the data centre is typically driven by a desire for consolidation of physical servers to reduce the amount of space\, power\, and money associated with data centre hardware.  Soon after consolidation\, the adoption of the concept of aggregation follows\, whereby enterprises provide capacity on demandthrough combining storage and server resources based on underlying virtualization.  The wide proliferation of virtualization then leads to automation and management of the virtualized environments through technologies such as self-service provisioning\, automated disaster recovery\, and release management for applications.  The objective of cloud transition management is to achieve a target state that meets the strategy requirements while minimizing business impact.  The benefits of these activities include helping customers to successfully complete transition to the cloud by leveraging EMC?s best practices and extensive experience to execute workload migration plans with minimized risk to continued business operations.
column38: SFIA Definitions Rate Card with rates FINAL 19Dec2011.doc

column30: As customers look to define and categorize cloud services to be consistent with industry thinking\, what methodology should they use to determine which applications can benefit from deployment in the cloud? How should customers assess readiness of individual applications for cloud-based deployment?  The financial and other benefits customers can come to expect from adopting a cloud-based deployment model from industry leading suppliers like EMC result from leveraging cloud services on a large scale.  Cloud services need to address technology\, people\, and process\, utilising a decision framework and governance model that include factors such as cost\, quality\, regulatory and legal\, and security. EMC has the expertise and breadth of experience to deliver cloud strategy from assessment to implementation.
column38: SFIA Definitions Rate Card with rates FINAL 19Dec2011.doc

column30: Organisations deploying ECM business solutions incorporating document capture\, enterprise content & case management\, customer communication management and information governance do so to increase business efficiency\, drive content re-use and knowledge management\, on a globally scalable\, secure infrastructure.  EMC Information Intelligence Group?s (IIG) Consulting organisation deliver specialist strategic and technical consulting services in the field of Enterprise Content Management that help prioritise the business needs\, deliver relevant business applications whilst focusing on future architecture\, industry trends and accelerating the time-to-value with the lowering of implementation risks & costs.  The cloud delivery model as an alternate delivery mechanism compared to self-managed\, on-premise solutions\, provides additional benefits for customers in the fact that optimally installed and configured platforms & solutions are readily provided ? almost eliminating specialist effort required around sizing & architecture and multiple installations\, reducing any start-up time from months to days.  ECM Cloud Solutions Delivery delivers ECM cloud ready business applications (workloads) with IIG Consulting?s ECM project delivery experiences and proven methodology\, but with the additional considerations and advantages of a private-cloud deployment model. This encapsulates a complete end-to-end project lifecycle from business requirements capture\, implementation\, testing\, deployment\, through to Service Management & Support options.

column30: Cloud Programme & Project Management - Atos programme and project management methodologies are based on industry and Office of Government Commerce (OGC) best practice. A company-wide forum standardises our approach\, shares information and ensures a consistent methodology to the highest industry benchmark standards. ? Transition to Cloud - Atos has a fully proven Transition to Support Methodology to allow us to seamlessly transition from the existing support arrangements with minimum disruption to client?s systems and users. This support methodology is known as CSDM (Continuous Service Delivery Model) and is based on the principles of ITIL (IT Infrastructure Library)\, the industry standard for delivery of IT Service management. ? Requirements management - Atos has developed a Requirements Management (RM) process to support our solution delivery to clients. The Atos approach to Requirements Management supports collaborative working that takes the business centric approach to engage stakeholders and establishes an assured foundation for system delivery. ? Test and acceptance ? a comprehensive suite of testing and acceptance services developed in line with industry best practice. We use a risk based test approach to prioritise the depth\, scheduling and coverage of testing. The V-Model is used as the model for describing how testing verifies and validates the system against the many levels of system definition from initial market\, business and service needs through to detail design. ? Training services - Atos Training Services are designed with your business goals in mind. column30: The Cloud Opportunity Assessment is designed to help clients identify applications\, either existing or to be developed\, for which Cloud Computing could deliver significant benefit. The Assessment collects and reports upon the existing IT infrastructure\, applications and project portfolio considering each system and inactive for its Cloud potential. Taking into consideration this potential a Cloud Roadmap is developed along with a business case. The high priority candidates can then be selected for potential pilot initiatives. The Cloud Opportunity Assessment allows clients to assess the value Cloud computing offers as a disruptive transformational technology\, whilst also de-risking investment in a market that is not yet fully mature. Depending upon the agreed scope of the assessment and any selected pilot(s)\, engagement duration is typically between 2 and 6 months.

column30: The Cloud Security Assessment is designed to help clients balance the significant potential benefits of Cloud with the challenges around trust and confidence related to security. The Assessment considers the key business issues\, legal\, confidentiality\, non-disclosure and intellectual property etc. that either prevent Cloud adoption or put at risk services being run from the Cloud. Business benefits such as the security afforded by the scale and standardisation of Cloud are also considered. Taking into account the risks and benefits a set of core security principles can be developed\, security levels can be increased and best practice rules developed to handle ignorance of data\, processing and application location. The Cloud Security Assessment allows clients to understand their current or potential risk exposure and make a confident move into the Cloud or reduce risk in their current operation. Depending upon the agreed scope of the assessment engagement duration is typically between 2 and 4 months.

SAM Portal from License Dashboard is the first Software Asset Management (SAM) solution truly to connect everyone involved in managing software on the network ? end users\, line managers\, IT\, procurement and compliance. All  stakeholders across the organisation can use a common cloud-based platform to request new software\, approve requests\, check license availability\, administer license transfers and  much more. Developed to conform with both the ISO 19770-1 SAM standard and Microsoft SAM Optimization Model\, SAM Portal is a cloud-based application designed to help organisations move to a higher level of SAM maturity by establishing and enforcing a structured workflow covering every step of the software management lifecycle.

OnDemand Migration for Email securely migrates users and data to Office 365 and Live@edu email platforms without requiring organisations to install or maintain any software for the move.  OnDemand Migration offers two services for organisations based on their migration needs and requirements: organisations can either migrate multiple users simultaneously or self-service offering enables end users to easily migrate themselves ? even if they have little technical knowledge or experience.

column30: The Squiz Cloud is a fully managed cloud-hosting environment - run by Squiz\, for Squiz products and solutions. It delivers a scalable\, robust and secure online infrastructure allowing you to realise the full value of the Squiz Suite. By leveraging Cloud technologies\, we can deliver richer\, more engaging online solutions for your prospects\, customers and staff.

You may wish Squiz to provide ongoing support services such as software upgrades\, 24x7 emergency support\, a single point of contact and priority help desk access with response time and uptime guarantees. We do this via a Service Level Agreement\, which is a formal agreement between Squiz and a client that is tailored to meet your particular needs\, expectations and requirements for the support of your Squiz system. Service Level Agreements can be used to support Squiz Solutions hosted on infrastructures other than the Squiz Cloud.

PDMS? Controlled Document Portal (CDP) enables you to share
the most up-to-date versions of key documents with your
colleagues\, partners and customers\, through a simple\, secure\,
online portal. To find out more\, visit gcloud.pdms.com

The CDP is both a simplified ?extranet?\, and an intuitive online
filing system. It helps you ensure that by default\, the most
recently published versions of documents are accessed\, by the
right people\, at the right time - wherever they are in the world.

The CDP has a wide range of features including: document
search\, document version control (including notification emails
when changes are made)\, document audit trails and document
archiving. Documents in the CDP can be accessed via the Internet
or via a ?mapped? network drive within your organization.

The service definition of the CDP can be found at:
gcloud.pdms.com/Resources/CDPServiceDefinition.pdf
